/*
  # Replace Categories and Seed Mock Courses

  ## Summary
  This migration replaces the 6 existing generic training categories with 10 industry-aligned
  categories based on Australia's most in-demand vocational training sectors, then seeds
  40-50 mock courses (4-5 per category) representative of real qualifications in demand.

  ## Changes

  ### 1. Categories (Replaced)
  Removes the 6 old categories and inserts 10 new ones ranked by national demand:
  1. Aged Care, Disability and Individual Support
  2. Health, Nursing and Allied Health Support
  3. Early Childhood Education and Care
  4. Construction, Building and Civil Trades
  5. Electrotechnology and Clean Energy
  6. Digital, IT and Cyber Security
  7. Training, Assessment and VET
  8. Hospitality, Tourism and Commercial Cookery
  9. Transport, Logistics and Supply Chain
  10. Manufacturing, Defence and Sovereign Capability

  ### 2. Courses (New)
  Inserts 4-5 courses per category, all published, with realistic durations,
  mixed difficulty levels, and AUD pricing.

  ### Security
  Existing RLS policies on both tables remain in place — no changes needed.

  ### Notes
  - Uses DELETE + INSERT pattern (safe — no FK dependents since courses table was empty)
  - All courses marked is_published = true so they appear on the public catalogue
  - A handful marked is_featured = true for the home page
*/

-- Clear existing seed data (courses first due to FK, then categories)
DELETE FROM courses;
DELETE FROM categories;

-- Insert 10 new industry-aligned categories

-- Seed courses: Aged Care, Disability and Individual Support (5 courses)

-- Seed courses: Health, Nursing and Allied Health Support (5 courses)

-- Seed courses: Early Childhood Education and Care (5 courses)

-- Seed courses: Construction, Building and Civil Trades (5 courses)

